      "content": "that makes sense. i'm just worried because my margins are already pretty tight. some people say that raising the wage is just about being \"fair\" to workers, but it feels like that's ignoring the reality of running a shop. does the data actually back up the idea that these hikes help the local economy in places like this, or is it mostly just an idealistic argument?",
