    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a bit hard to wrap my head around though. if i have to pay my staff way more just to hit those targets, i'm probably gonna have to cut staff or raise my prices. that would actually leave my customers with less money to spend here, right? it feels like the \"positive feedback loop\" argument ignores the fact that the money is being taken directly out of a small business's pocket. isn't that just transferring wealth from local owners to workers in a way that might actually hurt the town in the long run?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
